:return: Efficiency metric of the code snippet.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        visitor = ComplexityVisitor.from_code(code_snippet)\\n        efficiency_metric = visitor.total_complexity\\n        self.code_efficiency_metrics[code_snippet] = efficiency_metric\\n        return efficiency_metric\\n\\n    def estimate_build_time(self):\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        Estimate the build time based on the complexity of the code snippets.\\n\\n        :return: Estimated build time.\\n        \\"\\"\\"\\n        total_complexity = sum(self.code_efficiency_metrics.values())\\n        # Simplified estimation: 1 minute per complexity point\\n        estimated_time = total_complexity\\n        return estimated_time\\n\\n# Example usage\\nif __name__ == \\"__main__\\":\\n    optimizer = CollaborativeBuildOptimizer()\\n    optimizer.add_task(\\"task1\\")\\n    optimizer.add_task(\\"task2\\", dependencies=[\\"task1\\"])\\n    code_snippet = \\"def foo(): return 42\\"\\n    optimizer.analyze_code(code_snippet)\\n    print(optimizer.estimate_build_time())"\n}\n```\n\nThis JSON output includes a more complete version of `solution.py` based on the provided snippets and typical methods for a project management system. The `CollaborativeBuildOptimizer` class includes methods for adding tasks, analyzing code, and estimating build times. The example usage at the bottom demonstrates how to use the class. \n\nPlease note that this is a simplified version and may need further development to fully meet the requirements of the `TeamSyncPro` application.', 'continue_simulation': True, 'communications': [], 'total_milestones': 0, 'agent_kpis': {}}], 'planning_scores': [-1, -1, -1, -1, -1], 'communication_scores': [-1, -1, -1, -1, -1], 'token_usage': 95896, 'agent_kpis': {}, 'total_milestones': 0}
